# update using previous data within 66 days at the same time, which is not meant by the author.
def single_vol_r(date, time, deg_B = 6, deg_P = 5, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str, time_str = time_str, plot = False, get_workspace = False):
    # Skip the first day
    log_returns = log_returns[389:]
    date_str = date_str[1:]

    # Initialize the parameters
    # Number of days for warm-up is 167.
    # 100 for calculating long-term volatility.
    fast_num, slow_num = 50, 100
    # 66 for setting up a window for forecasting.
    fore_num = 66
    # lambda equals to 0.79, but 0.94 works better
    lam = 0.94

    # Set up the constant workspace
    vol_date = date_str[slow_num + fore_num + 1:]
    true_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[11:19] >= time_str[0] and x[5:10] >= vol_date[0]).values]
    if get_workspace:
        return true_return, vol_date

    # Set up the time-varying workspace
    # The adjustment 2 consists of slow sample adjustment (1) and current volatility ratio (1)
    temp_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[11:19] == time and x[5:10] <= date).values][- slow_num - fore_num - 2:]

    temp_slow_vol = pd.Series(0, index = temp_return[slow_num + 1:].index)
    temp_fast_vol = pd.Series(0, index = temp_return[slow_num + 1:].index)

    slow_lam = np.array([lam ** i for i in range(slow_num + 1)][::-1])
    for index in range(temp_return[slow_num + 1:].shape[0]):
        cur_slow_return_2 = temp_return[0 + index: slow_num + 1 + index].values ** 2
        slow_sum_lam = cur_slow_return_2 * slow_lam
        fast_sum_lam = slow_sum_lam[50:]
        temp_slow_vol.iloc[index] = np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(slow_sum_lam))
        temp_fast_vol.iloc[index] = np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(fast_sum_lam))
    temp_r_vol = temp_fast_vol / temp_slow_vol
    temp_spline = temp_r_vol[:-1]
    mean_return = (temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1] - temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].mean()) / temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].std()

    X, y = np.sort(temp_spline), np.sort(mean_return)
    if plot == True:
        x_pred = np.linspace(min(X), max(X), 100)
        # B-spline
        t, c, k = interpolate.splrep(X, y, t = np.quantile(X, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B + 2)[1:-1]))
        y_pred_B = interpolate.BSpline(t, c, k)(x_pred)
        # Polynominal Regression
        poly_reg = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P)
        X_poly = poly_reg.fit_transform(X.reshape(-1, 1))
        regressor = LinearRegression()
        regressor.fit(X_poly, y.reshape(-1, 1))
        y_pred_P = regressor.predict(poly_reg.fit_transform(x_pred.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten();
        # Plot
        plt.title("BSpline curve fitting")
        plt.plot(X, y, 'ro', label="original")
        plt.plot(x_pred, y_pred_B, '-c', label="B-spline")
        plt.plot(x_pred, y_pred_P, '-g', label="Polynomial")
        plt.legend(loc='best', fancybox=True, shadow=True)
        plt.grid()
    else:
        if temp_r_vol[-1:].values[0] == temp_r_vol.min():
            curr_r = pd.Series(temp_spline.min() ,index = temp_r_vol[-1:].index)
        elif temp_r_vol[-1:].values[0] == temp_r_vol.max():
            curr_r = pd.Series(temp_spline.max() ,index = temp_r_vol[-1:].index)
        else:
            curr_r = temp_r_vol[-1:]
        # B-spline
        t, c, k = interpolate.splrep(X, y, t = np.quantile(X, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B + 2)[1:-1]))
        B_spline_vol_r = interpolate.BSpline(t, c, k)(curr_r) * temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].std() + temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].mean()
        # Polynominal Regression
        poly_reg = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P)
        X_poly = poly_reg.fit_transform(X.reshape(-1, 1))
        regressor = LinearRegression()
        regressor.fit(X_poly, y.reshape(-1, 1))
        P_spline_vol_r = regressor.predict(poly_reg.fit_transform(curr_r.values.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten() * temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].std() + temp_return[slow_num + 1: -1].mean()
        return curr_r.index, B_spline_vol_r[0], P_spline_vol_r[0]

def generate_spline(log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # Initialize the parameters
    # Number of days for warm-up is 167.
    # 100 for calculating long-term volatility.
    fast_num, slow_num = 50, 100
    # 66 for setting up a window for forecasting.
    N, n_star = 252, 66
    # lambda equals to 0.79
    lam = 0.94
    # Parameters for B-spline and Polynomial-spline
    deg_B_v, deg_B_s = 6, 10
    deg_P_v, deg_P_s = 5, 8
    # Set the first day as warm-up day
    date_str = date_str[1:]
    # Generate results DataFrame
    cur_X_vol_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_X_sea_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_hat_vol_B_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_hat_sea_B_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_hat_comb_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_hat_vol_P_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    cur_return_hat_sea_P_all = pd.DataFrame([])
    for i in range(n_star + 1, N + 1):
        # Step 1. Get the batch - prev_return
        all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[i - 67: i]).values]
        prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-390:]

        # Step 2. Normalize the batch - norm_prev_return
        norm_prev_return = (prev_return - prev_return.mean()) / prev_return.std()

        # Step 3(1). Get the inputs for volatility ratio - prev_X_vol & cur_X_vol
        all_X_vol = pd.Series(0, index = all_return.index)
        for i in range(all_return.shape[0]):
            loop_item = all_return[i: i+1]
            loop_index = (np.array(log_returns.index) == np.array(loop_item.index)).argmax()
            loop_return_sq = log_returns[loop_index - 100: loop_index + 1] ** 2
            loop_lam = pd.Series([lam ** i for i in range(100 + 1)][::-1], index = loop_return_sq.index)
            loop_slow = loop_return_sq * loop_lam
            loop_fast = loop_slow[50:]
            loop_X_vol = np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(loop_fast)) / np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(loop_slow))
            all_X_vol[loop_item.index] = loop_X_vol
        prev_X_vol, cur_X_vol = all_X_vol[:-390], all_X_vol[-390:]

        # Step 3(2). Get the inputs for seasonality - prev_X_sea & cur_X_sea
        all_X_sea = pd.Series(0, index = all_return.index)
        for i in range(all_return.shape[0]):
            loop_item = all_return[i: i+1]
            all_X_sea[loop_item.index] = i % 390 + 1
        prev_X_sea, cur_X_sea = all_X_sea[:-390], all_X_sea[-390:]

        # Step 4. Generate the B-spline and Polynomial-spline
        x_sea, y_sea = prev_X_sea, norm_prev_return
        x_sea, y_sea = x_sea[np.argsort(x_sea)].values, y_sea[np.argsort(x_sea)].values
        x_vol, y_vol = prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return
        x_vol, y_vol = x_vol[np.argsort(x_vol)].values, y_vol[np.argsort(x_vol)].values
        # B-Spline - Volatility Ratio
        t_vol, c_vol, k_vol = interpolate.splrep(x_vol, y_vol, t = np.quantile(x_vol, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_v  + 2)[1:-1]))
        # B-Spline - Seasonality
        t_sea, c_sea, k_sea = interpolate.splrep(x_sea, y_sea, t = np.quantile(x_sea, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_s  + 2)[1:-1]))
        # Polynominal Spline - Volatility Ratio
        poly_reg_vol = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P_v)
        x_vol_poly = poly_reg_vol.fit_transform(x_vol.reshape(-1, 1))
        regressor_vol = LinearRegression()
        regressor_vol.fit(x_vol_poly, y_vol.reshape(-1, 1))
        # Polynominal Spline - Seasonality
        poly_reg_sea = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P_s)
        x_sea_poly = poly_reg_sea.fit_transform(x_sea.reshape(-1, 1))
        regressor_sea = LinearRegression()
        regressor_sea.fit(x_sea_poly, y_sea.reshape(-1, 1))
        # B-Spline - Combine
        x, y, z = prev_X_sea, prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return
        # sort data to avoid plotting problems
        x, y, z = zip(*sorted(zip(x, y, z)))
        tck = interpolate.bisplrep(x, y, z, tx = np.quantile(x, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_s  + 2)[1:-1]), ty = np.quantile(y, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_v  + 2)[1:-1]))

        # Step 5(1). Evaluate the splines - B-spline case
        cur_return_hat_vol_B = prev_return.std() * interpolate.BSpline(t_vol, c_vol, k_vol)(cur_X_vol) + prev_return.mean()
        cur_return_hat_sea_B = prev_return.std() * interpolate.BSpline(t_sea, c_sea, k_sea)(cur_X_sea) + prev_return.mean()
        cur_return_hat_vol_B = pd.Series(cur_return_hat_vol_B, index = cur_return.index)
        cur_return_hat_sea_B = pd.Series(cur_return_hat_sea_B, index = cur_return.index)
        cur_return_hat_comb = prev_return.std() * interpolate.bisplev(cur_X_sea.values, cur_X_vol[np.argsort(cur_X_vol)].values, tck) + prev_return.mean()
        cur_return_hat_comb = np.array([cur_return_hat_comb[i[0], i[1]] for i in zip(np.argsort(cur_X_sea).values, np.argsort(np.argsort(cur_X_vol)).values)])
        cur_return_hat_comb = pd.Series(cur_return_hat_comb, index = cur_return.index)

        # Step 5(2). Evaluate the splines - Polynominal Spline case
        cur_return_hat_vol_P = regressor_vol.predict(poly_reg_vol.fit_transform(cur_X_vol.values.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten();
        cur_return_hat_sea_P = regressor_sea.predict(poly_reg_sea.fit_transform(cur_X_sea.values.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten();
        cur_return_hat_vol_P = prev_return.std() * pd.Series(cur_return_hat_vol_P, index = cur_return.index) + prev_return.mean()
        cur_return_hat_sea_P = prev_return.std() * pd.Series(cur_return_hat_sea_P, index = cur_return.index) + prev_return.mean()

        # Store results
        cur_X_vol_all = pd.concat([cur_X_vol_all, cur_X_vol])
        cur_X_sea_all = pd.concat([cur_X_sea_all, cur_X_sea])
        cur_return_all = pd.concat([cur_return_all, cur_return])
        cur_return_hat_vol_B_all = pd.concat([cur_return_hat_vol_B_all, cur_return_hat_vol_B])
        cur_return_hat_sea_B_all = pd.concat([cur_return_hat_sea_B_all, cur_return_hat_sea_B])
        cur_return_hat_comb_all = pd.concat([cur_return_hat_comb_all, cur_return_hat_comb])
        cur_return_hat_vol_P_all = pd.concat([cur_return_hat_vol_P_all, cur_return_hat_vol_P])
        cur_return_hat_sea_P_all = pd.concat([cur_return_hat_sea_P_all, cur_return_hat_sea_P])

    cur_X_vol_all.to_csv("X_vol.csv")
    cur_X_sea_all.to_csv("X_sea.csv")
    cur_return_all.to_csv("true_return.csv")
    cur_return_hat_vol_B_all.to_csv("return_hat_vol_B.csv")
    cur_return_hat_sea_B_all.to_csv("return_hat_sea_B.csv")
    cur_return_hat_comb_all.to_csv("return_hat_comb.csv")
    cur_return_hat_vol_P_all.to_csv("return_hat_vol_P.csv")
    cur_return_hat_sea_P_all.to_csv("return_hat_sea_P.csv")

def generate_signal_coef(log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # 66 for setting up a window for forecasting.
    N, n_star = 252, 66
    # Set the first day as warm-up day
    date_str = date_str[1:]
    # Generate results DataFrame
    signal_coef = pd.DataFrame([], dtype = float, columns = ["mean", "std"])
    for i in range(n_star + 1, N + 1):
        all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[i - 67: i]).values]
        prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-390:]
        signal_coef.loc[cur_return.index[0][0:10], "mean"] = prev_return.mean()
        signal_coef.loc[cur_return.index[0][0:10], "std"] = prev_return.std()
    return signal_coef

def convert_signal(df, signal_coef = signal_coef):
    temp_df = df.copy()
    for i in range(signal_coef.index.shape[0]):
        index = pd.Series(temp_df.index, index = temp_df.index).apply(lambda x: x[0:10] == signal_coef.index[i]).values
        temp_df.loc[index] = (temp_df.loc[index] - signal_coef["mean"][i]) / signal_coef["std"][i]
    temp_df[temp_df > 1], temp_df[temp_df < -1] = 1, -1
    return temp_df

def Sharpe(wealth_df, time_str = time_str):
    daily_wealth = wealth_df[pd.Series(wealth_df.index, index = wealth_df.index).apply(lambda x: x[11:19] == time_str[-1]).values]
    daily_wealth = pd.DataFrame([1] + list(daily_wealth.values.flatten()))
    daily_return = np.log((daily_wealth / daily_wealth.shift(1)).dropna())
    return (np.sqrt(daily_return.shape[0]) * daily_return.mean() / daily_return.std()).values[0], daily_return.values.flatten()

def correlation_matrix(df):
    # Display correlation matrix
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6));
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1)
    sns1 = sns.heatmap(data=df.corr(), vmin=0, vmax=1, ax=ax1, cmap ="RdBu_r", annot=True, fmt=".4f", annot_kws={"fontsize":14})
    cbar = sns1.collections[0].colorbar
    cbar.ax.tick_params(labelsize=14)
    plt.xticks(fontsize=14, rotation = 30, horizontalalignment="right");
    plt.yticks(fontsize=14);

def train_spline(index, log_returns = log_returns, date_str = date_str):
    # Initialize the parameters
    # Number of days for warm-up is 167.
    # 100 for calculating long-term volatility.
    fast_num, slow_num = 50, 100
    # 66 for setting up a window for forecasting.
    N, n_star = 252, 66
    # lambda equals to 0.79
    lam = 0.94
    # Set the first day as warm-up day
    date_str = date_str[1:]

    # There are totally 252 - 67 + 1 = 186 samples.
    # So index is from 0 to 185.
    if type(index) != int or index < 0 or index > 185:
        raise Exception("Index is wrong. It should be an integer between [0, 185]!")

    # Step 1. Get the batch - prev_return
    all_return = log_returns[pd.Series(log_returns.index, index = log_returns.index).apply(lambda x: x[5:10] in date_str[index: index + 67]).values]
    prev_return, cur_return = all_return[:-390], all_return[-390:]

    # Step 2. Normalize the batch - norm_prev_return
    norm_prev_return = (prev_return - prev_return.mean()) / prev_return.std()

    # Step 3(1). Get the inputs for volatility ratio - prev_X_vol & cur_X_vol
    all_X_vol = pd.Series(0, index = all_return.index)
    for i in range(all_return.shape[0]):
        loop_item = all_return[i: i+1]
        loop_index = (np.array(log_returns.index) == np.array(loop_item.index)).argmax()
        loop_return_sq = log_returns[loop_index - 100: loop_index + 1] ** 2
        loop_lam = pd.Series([lam ** i for i in range(100 + 1)][::-1], index = loop_return_sq.index)
        loop_slow = loop_return_sq * loop_lam
        loop_fast = loop_slow[50:]
        loop_X_vol = np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(loop_fast)) / np.sqrt((1 - lam) * np.sum(loop_slow))
        all_X_vol[loop_item.index] = loop_X_vol
    prev_X_vol, cur_X_vol = all_X_vol[:-390], all_X_vol[-390:]

    # Step 3(2). Get the inputs for seasonality - prev_X_sea & cur_X_sea
    all_X_sea = pd.Series(0, index = all_return.index)
    for i in range(all_return.shape[0]):
        loop_item = all_return[i: i+1]
        all_X_sea[loop_item.index] = i % 390 + 1
    prev_X_sea, cur_X_sea = all_X_sea[:-390], all_X_sea[-390:]

    return prev_X_sea, prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return, prev_return

def plot_spline(train_set):
    prev_X_sea, prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return, prev_return = train_set
    # Parameters for B-spline and Polynomial-spline
    deg_B_v, deg_B_s = 6, 10
    deg_P_v, deg_P_s = 5, 8

    # Step 4(1). Generate the B-spline and Polynomial-spline
    x_sea, y_sea = prev_X_sea, norm_prev_return
    x_sea, y_sea = x_sea[np.argsort(x_sea)].values, y_sea[np.argsort(x_sea)].values
    x_vol, y_vol = prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return
    x_vol, y_vol = x_vol[np.argsort(x_vol)].values, y_vol[np.argsort(x_vol)].values

    # B-Spline - Volatility Ratio
    t_vol, c_vol, k_vol = interpolate.splrep(x_vol, y_vol, t = np.quantile(x_vol, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_v  + 2)[1:-1]))
    # B-Spline - Seasonality
    t_sea, c_sea, k_sea = interpolate.splrep(x_sea, y_sea, t = np.quantile(x_sea, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_s  + 2)[1:-1]))
    # Polynominal Spline - Volatility Ratio
    poly_reg_vol = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P_v)
    x_vol_poly = poly_reg_vol.fit_transform(x_vol.reshape(-1, 1))
    regressor_vol = LinearRegression()
    regressor_vol.fit(x_vol_poly, y_vol.reshape(-1, 1))
    # Polynominal Spline - Seasonality
    poly_reg_sea = PolynomialFeatures(degree = deg_P_s)
    x_sea_poly = poly_reg_sea.fit_transform(x_sea.reshape(-1, 1))
    regressor_sea = LinearRegression()
    regressor_sea.fit(x_sea_poly, y_sea.reshape(-1, 1))

    # Step 4(2). Fit the splines and prepare for plotting
    x_sea_plot = np.arange(1, 391)
    x_vol_plot = np.linspace(x_vol.min(), x_vol.max(), 100)
    y_vol_plot_B = interpolate.BSpline(t_vol, c_vol, k_vol)(x_vol_plot)
    y_sea_plot_B = interpolate.BSpline(t_sea, c_sea, k_sea)(x_sea_plot)
    y_vol_plot_P = regressor_vol.predict(poly_reg_vol.fit_transform(x_vol_plot.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten();
    y_sea_plot_P = regressor_sea.predict(poly_reg_sea.fit_transform(x_sea_plot.reshape(-1, 1))).flatten();

    # To ensure the consistency with the author's work, we do not transform them to original state.
    # y_vol = prev_return.std() * y_vol + prev_return.mean()
    # y_vol_plot_B = prev_return.std() * y_vol_plot_B + prev_return.mean()
    # y_vol_plot_P = prev_return.std() * y_vol_plot_P + prev_return.mean()
    # y_sea = prev_return.std() * y_sea + prev_return.mean()
    # y_sea_plot_B = prev_return.std() * y_sea_plot_B + prev_return.mean()
    # y_sea_plot_P = prev_return.std() * y_sea_plot_P + prev_return.mean()

    # Plot - Volatility Ratio
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6));
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1);

    ax1.plot(x_vol, y_vol, 'ro', label="original");
    ax1.plot(x_vol_plot, y_vol_plot_B , '-c', label="B-spline");
    ax1.plot(x_vol_plot, y_vol_plot_P, '-g', label="Polynomial");
    xlim, ylim = ax1.get_xlim(), ax1.get_ylim();

    ax1.set_xlim(xlim[0], xlim[1] - 0.03);
    ax1.set_ylim(-0.06, 0.06);

    plt.legend(loc='best', fancybox=True, shadow=True);
    plt.title("BSpline curve fitting");
    plt.grid();

    # Plot - Seasonality
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2);
    ax2.plot(x_sea_plot, y_sea_plot_B , '-c', label="B-spline", zorder=2);
    ax2.plot(x_sea_plot, y_sea_plot_P, '-g', label="Polynomial", zorder=2);
    xlim, ylim = ax2.get_xlim(), ax2.get_ylim();
    ax2.plot(x_sea, y_sea, 'ro', label="original", zorder = 1);

    ax2.set_xlim(xlim[0], xlim[1] - 0.03);
    ax2.set_ylim(ylim[0], ylim[1]);

    plt.legend(loc='best', fancybox=True, shadow=True);
    plt.title("BSpline curve fitting");
    plt.grid();

def plot_spline_3d(train_set):
    prev_X_sea, prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return, prev_return = train_set
    # Parameters for B-spline and Polynomial-spline
    deg_B_v, deg_B_s = 6, 10
    deg_P_v, deg_P_s = 5, 8

    x, y, z = prev_X_sea, prev_X_vol, norm_prev_return
    # sort data to avoid plotting problems
    x, y, z = zip(*sorted(zip(x, y, z)))

    tck = interpolate.bisplrep(x, y, z, tx = np.quantile(x, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_s  + 2)[1:-1]), ty = np.quantile(y, np.linspace(0, 1, deg_B_v  + 2)[1:-1]))
    x_grid = np.linspace(min(x),max(x), int(len(x)/10))
    y_grid = np.linspace(min(y),max(y), int(len(y)/10))
    Z = interpolate.bisplev(x_grid, y_grid, tck)
    #Z = prev_return.std() * Z + prev_return.mean()

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(projection='3d')

    x_plot, y_plot = np.meshgrid(x_grid, y_grid)
    surf = ax.plot_surface(x_plot, y_plot, Z, cmap=cm.cool, vmin=-0.3, vmax=0.3)
    fig.colorbar(surf)
    ax.set_zlim(-0.2, 0.2)
